Acquired identifiable intangible assets are classified into three categories: (1) goodwill, (2) intangible assets with finite lives subject to amortization and (3) intangible assets with indefinite lives. Goodwill and intangible assets with indefinite lives are not amortized; rather, they are reviewed for impairment at least annually. 

GOODWILL 

Goodwill is recognized when the consideration paid for a business exceeds the fair value of the tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired. Goodwill is allocated to reporting units for purposes of testing goodwill for impairment. 

During the third quarter of 2022, we recorded an interim goodwill impairment loss of $ 50.9 million related to the fourth quarter sale of a reporting unit comprised of concrete operations in New Jersey, New York and Pennsylvania. There were no charges for goodwill impairment in the years ended December 31, 2021 and 2020. Accumulated goodwill impairment losses amount to $ 303.6 million ($ 252.7 million in our former Cement segment and $ 50.9 in our Concrete segment). 

